<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12102h"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12102h">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12102h"> 102(h)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> deceitful ox</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Then I told him about an ox, who, when he didn&apos;t want to work, pretended to be dead. Rolf now got very excited, and wanted to go on rapping&mdash;first on my hand, and then on the leather-covered sofa on which I was sitting. I became rather uneasy and got him to go and rap to Fr&auml;ulein Moekel, for I could then follow the raps far better. And what he now had to say referred to <mark>the deceitful ox</mark>&mdash;it was: &ldquo;Hat Recht: Lol immer sagen Bauchweh!&rdquo; (= Quite right of him! Lol always says he has a pain in his stomach!) <small> Henny Kindermann, <a name="LOLA" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#LOLA"><cite title="source">Lola or the thought and speech of animals</cite></a> (1922) 28</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
